<header class="entry-header">
			<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.backupcentral.com/is-your-data-protection-company-worried-about-gdpr-they-should-be/" title="Permalink to Is your data protection company worried about GDPR? They should be." rel="bookmark">Is your data protection company worried about GDPR? They should be.</a></h1>
	
		<div class="entry-meta">
		Posted on <a href="http://www.backupcentral.com/is-your-data-protection-company-worried-about-gdpr-they-should-be/" title="3:12 am" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2018-03-12T03:12:17+00:00" pubdate>March 12, 2018</time></a><span class="byline"> by <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://www.backupcentral.com/author/admin/" title="View all posts by W. Curtis Preston" rel="author">W. Curtis Preston</a></span></span>	</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->	
				<div class="entry-content">
			<p>If you haven&#8217;t looked into how your data protection vendors are preparing for the General Data Protection Regulation (GPDR), you&#8217;re already behind the power curve.  It goes into effect May 25, 2018. Hopefully this article can get you up to speed so you can start pressuring your vendors about how they are going to help you comply with this incredibly big regulation.</p>
